---
import DigiLayout from '~/layouts/DigiLayout.astro';
import { site } from '~/data/digiclara';
---
<DigiLayout lang="en" title="About us" description="What DigiClara is and how its editorial lead works.">
  <section class="section"><div class="page-shell article-body">
    <p class="eyebrow">About DigiClara</p>
    <h1>Clarity, independence and practical technology</h1>
    <p>DigiClara is an independent blog created to explain digital security, privacy, Windows, networks and safe software in clear language.</p>
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>We help people, families and small businesses make better digital decisions without promising absolute security or pushing unnecessary purchases.</p>
    <h2>Editorial lead</h2>
    <p>The site is led by {site.ownerName}, from Spain. Editorial contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>
    <h2>Independence</h2>
    <p>DigiClara currently shows no advertising, uses no affiliate links and has no official social profiles. If a future commercial relationship exists, it must be clearly identified.</p>
    <h2>How we research</h2>
    <p>We prioritise official documentation, public organisations, privacy policies and stable technical sources. We separate documentary guides, documentary comparisons and practical tests when they have actually been performed.</p>
    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>If you find an error, you can email us. Relevant corrections are reviewed and reflected by updating the content date.</p>
  </div></section>
</DigiLayout>
